| `_resolve_tied(...)` | Applies H2H; still-tied sub-groups get `rng.shuffle()` (injected RNG, never global) |
| `_to_v4_row(...)` | Emits the football-data.org v4 row shape consumed by `resolve_r32` |
| `_get_played(state)` | Duck-typed: accepts both `.played` (real Pydantic `TournamentState`) and `.played_matches` (test stubs) |
| `_extract_scoreline(raw)` | Normalises sampler return as `tuple` or `ndarray shape (size,2)` |
| `GroupStageSimulator` | 3 class methods, all < 10 lines; injects sampler + rng |

**Tiebreak correctness**: The circular 3-way test (P→Q→Z→P, all 1-0) correctly exhausts H2H (each team gets 3 h2h pts / GD=0 / GF=1 in the mini-table) and falls through to `rng.shuffle()` — demonstrated to produce varying outcomes across 20+ seeds.
