> R32 seeding via `resolve_r32` and the round-folding reuse from `tournament.py` are sound. One interface gap to call out for the extra-time path: `ScorelineSampler.sample(home, away, neutral, size, random_state)` computes its λ internally from `TeamAbilities` and exposes no way to scale them — so you cannot honor `extra_time_factor` by calling `sample()` again. To sample ET goals at `λ × extra_time_factor` you must drop to the lower-level functions already in `poisson.py`: call `lambdas(abilities, home, away, neutral=True)`, multiply both rates by `extra_time_factor`, build a `score_matrix(lh*f, la*f, rho=abilities.rho, max_goals=...)`, and draw from it. Plan the resolver to take `TeamAbilities` (or the `lambdas`/`score_matrix` helpers), not just a `ScorelineSampler`, otherwise the ET requirement isn't implementable against the current API. Also specify that ET goals are ADDED to the drawn full-time score (not a replacement draw) before the penalty coin-flip check.

