2026-06-24 04:09:24,807 DEBUG msg #10: UserMessage tool_result(toolu_01WaRpELzarFMUDWcMDbMEFd): {"assignees":[{"id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMwOTUyOTQ4","login":"SilvioBaratto","name":"Silvio Angelo Baratto Roldan","databaseId":0}],"body":"## Goal\nTurn final group standings into the 16 concrete Round-of-32 ties via the WC2026 bracket template, then simulate the single-elimination tree (R32 → R16 → QF → SF → Final) where each tie is resolved by a sampled scoreline, with draws decided by extra-time (`λ × extra_time_factor`) then a penalty coin-flip.\n\n## Context\n`data/wc2026_bracket.py` encodes the slotting rules: `R32_SLOTS` (`wc2026_bracket.py:41-58`) is 16 `(home_slot, away_slot)` pairs using slot codes like `\"1A\"` (group A winner), `\"2A\"` (runner-up), `\"3ABCDF\"` (best-third placeholder). `resolve_r32(standings)` (`wc2026_bracket.py:174-180`) takes the v4-shaped standings dict and returns 16 concrete `(home_team, away_team)` pairs; `rank_third_places()` + `assign_thirds()` handle the 8-best-thirds selection internally.\n\n`simulation/poisson.py` `ScorelineSampler.sample(home, away, neutral, size, random_state)` (`poisson.py:241-256`) returns `(size, 2)` goal arrays; `lambdas(abilities, home, away, neutral)` (`poisson.py:72-82`) gives the expected goal rates needed to scale extra-time. The knockout extra-time multiplier (`extra_time_factor = 0.33`) and master seed come from the extended `SimulationConfig` (issue #16). WC2026 knockout venues are neutral.\n\nThe existing `simulation/tournament.py` `build_bracket_tree`/`extract_bracket_slots` (`tournament.py:85-163`) fold adjacent winners upward (round 0 = R32 … round 4 = Final) — reuse this pairing convention, but the existing `_play_tie` (`tournament.py:271-283`) uses the legacy classifier `GamePredictor` and has **no** draw/extra-time/penalty handling, so a new tie resolver is required. Per the project design choice, the `0.33` extra-time multiplier and coin-flip shootout are implementation choices (not standards).\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `resolve_r32(standings_dict)` is called to seed the 16 R32 ties; pairings match `R32_SLOTS` for given standings.\n- [ ] A single knockout tie is resolved by: sample a scoreline → if drawn, resample extra-time goals scaled by `extra_time_factor` → if still level, seeded penalty coin-flip → return the advancing team.\n- [ ] The full tree folds R32 → R16 → QF → SF → Final, producing one champion per simulated tournament.\n- [ ] All knockout matches treated as neutral venue.\n- [ ] Deterministic given a seed: identical standings + seed → identical champion.\n- [ ] All tests pass; new `tests/test_knockout.py` asserts R32 pairings, exercises the extra-time + penalty path with a stub sampler forcing a draw, and asserts seed reproducibility.\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #16: feat: Cycle 5 config groundwork — [rf]/[odds] sections, knockout sim params, TOML wiring\n- #17: feat: group-stage simulation engine with FIFA tiebreaks (simulation/group_stage.py)\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/simulation/knockout.py` — a `KnockoutSimulator` (or pure functions) that calls `wc2026_bracket.resolve_r32` for seeding and resolves each tie via sample → extra-time → penalty; reuse the round-folding convention from `tournament.py:85-132` (or its tree helpers) without modifying that file.\n- **Create:** `tests/test_knockout.py` — fixed final standings + stub sampler (force a draw to hit extra-time/penalty) → assert single winner, R32 pairing correctness, and determinism.\n- Consume `extra_time_factor` and the master seed from `SimulationConfig` (issue #16); inject a `numpy.random.Generator` for the penalty coin-flip.\n- Consumes the v4-dict standings shape produced by issue #17 — keep the interface aligned with that adapter.","labels":[{"id":"LA_