2026-06-24 04:24:00,851 DEBUG msg #11: UserMessage tool_result(toolu_01RVWhanA6LbytRzCpqNvhAB): {"assignees":[{"id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMwOTUyOTQ4","login":"SilvioBaratto","name":"Silvio Angelo Baratto Roldan","databaseId":0}],"body":"## Goal\nRun ~100,000 seeded Monte-Carlo tournaments (group-stage simulation + knockout) conditioned on played WC2026 results, and aggregate per-team **title odds** plus **per-round advancement probabilities** for all 48 teams. This is the central integration node that produces the live forecast.\n\n## Context\nThis orchestrator wires together the Cycle-5 simulation pieces:\n- `data/live.py` `fetch_tournament_state(client=None, competition=\"WC\")` (`live.py:151-158`) returns a `TournamentState` (played / remaining_group_fixtures / standings). It must run **no-key by default** — when no API key is present, fall back to the martj42 WC2026 schedule (martj42 already contains WC2026 fixtures with `tournament == \"FIFA World Cup\"`). The football-data.org key only refines live state.\n- `simulation/poisson.py` `fit_dixon_coles(df, config)` → `TeamAbilities`; `make_sampler(abilities, config)` → `ScorelineSampler` (`poisson.py:264-271`). Fit once on historical martj42 data, then reuse across all simulations.\n- The group-stage simulator (issue #17) produces final v4-shaped standings; the knockout simulator (issue #18) resolves R32 from those standings and folds to a champion.\n- `simulation/tournament.py` `RoundResult` (`tournament.py:31-61`) exposes `.probabilities = {team: count / n_simulations}` — reuse this contract so the plotter (issue #23) can consume per-round results unchanged.\n\nPerformance target: ~100k tournaments complete in seconds–low minutes. Determinism: a master seed derives per-iteration sub-seeds so two runs with the same seed produce identical odds.\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] Orchestrates: ingest `TournamentState` → fit/accept `TeamAbilities` once → loop N tournaments (group sim from #17 + knockout from #18) with per-iteration sub-seeds derived from a master seed → accumulate champion + round-reached counts.\n- [ ] Returns a `ForecastResult` value object with full title odds (champion probability per team, all 48 teams present) and `{round: probabilities}` per-round advancement reusing the `RoundResult.probabilities` contract.\n- [ ] Title-odds across all 48 teams sum to ≈ 1.0; per-round advancement counts match the number of slots in each round.\n- [ ] Runs **no-key by default** (martj42 WC2026 schedule); football-data.org key optional for live refinement; re-runnable after each matchday.\n- [ ] Deterministic: same master seed → identical odds across two runs.\n- [ ] ~100k tournaments complete in seconds–low minutes (document the measured timing).\n- [ ] All tests pass; new `tests/test_live_forecast.py` runs a small-N forecast with a stub sampler asserting probability sanity, 48-team coverage, and seed reproducibility.\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #16: feat: Cycle 5 config groundwork — [rf]/[odds] sections, knockout sim params, TOML wiring\n- #17: feat: group-stage simulation engine with FIFA tiebreaks (simulation/group_stage.py)\n- #18: feat: R32 resolution + single-elimination knockout sim with extra-time/penalties (simulation/knockout.py)\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/simulation/live_forecast.py` — orchestrator function/class returning `ForecastResult`; derive per-iteration sub-seeds from the `SimulationConfig.random_seed` (issue #16) via a `numpy.random.SeedSequence`/spawn pattern for reproducible parallel-safe streams.\n- **Create:** `tests/test_live_forecast.py` — small N (e.g. 200) with stub sampler: assert champion probs sum ≈ 1.0 over 48 teams, all teams present, two runs identical under same seed.\n- Keep the existing `simulation/tournament.py` untouched; this is a sibling orchestrator (do not overload the legacy classifier-based simulator).\n- Fit Dixon-Coles abilities **once** outside the Monte-Carlo loop for performance; vectorize scoreline sampling where possible (the sampler accepts `size=N`).\n- No-key default is a hard requirement — guard the live-adapter path so a missing key degrades to the martj42 schedule rather than raising.","labels":[{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIFhg","name":"priority:high","description":"High priority","color":"FF0000"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopII0g","name":"phase:implement","description":"Phase: implement","color":"D4C5F9"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIKMQ","name":"agent:python-pro","description":"Agent: python-pro","color":"7057FF"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACop6wtA","name":"area:simulation","description":"Area: simulation","color":"0052CC"}],"milestone":{"number":5,"title":"Cycle 5 — Tournament Simulation & Full Pipeline","description":"Extend tournament simulator: ingest played WC2026 results as fixed, simulate remaining group matches (correct tiebreak rules: goal-diff, goals-for, head-to-head, coin-flip), resolve Round of 32 from standings, simulate knockout (extra time λ×0.33 → penalty coin-flip), run ~100k Monte Carlo → full title odds + per-round advancement for all 48 teams. Historical odds scraper (backtest baseline: de-vig WC2014/18/22 from archived sources, cache to CSV). Evaluation metrics: RPS (primary), log-loss, Brier on time-aware splits. Config: add [poisson], [elo], [rf], [odds], [live] sections (Pydantic + TOML). CLI: new commands fetch-live, build-features, train-hybrid, backtest, forecast (live title odds) + existing bracket/PNG.","dueOn":null},"state":"OPEN","title":"feat: ~100k Monte-Carlo live-forecast orchestrator + title odds (simulation/live_forecast.py)"}
