t: results written to / read from CSV under `[odds].cache_dir`; a cached read needs no network.\n- [ ] Graceful degradation: a blocked/raising source falls back to cache (or empty frame) and **never** propagates an exception.\n- [ ] Team names normalized via `crosswalk.normalize_team`.\n- [ ] `beautifulsoup4` added to `pyproject.toml` dependencies.\n- [ ] All tests pass; new `tests/test_odds.py` parses saved HTML fixtures (no live network), asserts de-vig sums to 1.0, and asserts a simulated 403/exception triggers cache/empty fallback without raising.\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #16: feat: Cycle 5 config groundwork — [rf]/[odds] sections, knockout sim params, TOML wiring\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/data/odds.py` — `OddsScraper` with cache-first read/write, per-source `try/except` → cache/empty fallback, de-vig helper, and crosswalk normalization. Consume `AppConfig.odds`.\n- **Modify:** `pyproject.toml:13-21` — add `beautifulsoup4>=4.12` to `dependencies`.\n- **Modify:** `worldcup_playoff/data/__init__.py` — export the public scraper/loader entry point.\n- **Create:** `tests/test_odds.py` — fixture HTML strings parsed offline; de-vig math; blocked-source fallback. Do NOT hit live network in tests.\n- Bookmaker odds are an evaluation baseline ONLY — do not feed them into `features/build.py` or `models/hybrid.py`.\n- Verify nothing here breaks no-key default operation: odds are optional; absence must not break the forecast.","labels":[{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIFtA","name":"priority:medium","description":"Medium priority","color":"FBCA04"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopII0g","name":"phase:implement","description":"Phase: implement","color":"D4C5F9"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIKMQ","name":"agent:python-pro","description":"Agent: python-pro","color":"7057FF"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopKxrQ","name":"area:data","description":"Area: data","color":"005