116	## Data Contracts (probed live — exact schemas, build to these)
117	
118	> Verified by hitting the real endpoints/datasets on 2026-06-23. Build loaders to these exact shapes.
119	
120	### martj42/international_results (CC0, no key) — PRIMARY training + WC2026 schedule
121	- Base: `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/martj42/international_results/master/`
122	- `results.csv` — **49,477 rows**, columns:
123	  `date, home_team, away_team, home_score, away_score, tournament, city, country, neutral`
124	  - `home_score`/`away_score` are **`"NA"`** for unplayed fixtures → coerce to nullable Int.
125	  - `neutral` is the string **`"TRUE"`/`"FALSE"`** → parse to bool.
126	  - **Already contains WC2026 fixtures** (`tournament == "FIFA World Cup"`, scores `NA` until played,
127	    `neutral == TRUE`, `country == "United States"`). So martj42 alone provides the schedule + scores.
128	- `shootouts.csv` — **678 rows**: `date, home_team, away_team, winner, first_shooter` (penalty outcomes;
129	  use to validate/parametrize the knockout shootout model).
130	- `goalscorers.csv` — **47,741 rows**: `date, home_team, away_team, team, scorer, minute, own_goal, penalty`.
131	
132	### football-data.org v4 (key in `.env`, header `X-Auth-Token`, 10 req/min) — LIVE WC2026 only
133	- `GET /v4/competitions/WC/matches` → `{filters, resultSet{count,first,last,played}, competition, matches[]}`.
134	  - Currently **104 matches, 44 played** (mid group stage, matchday 2).
135	  - Each match: `id, utcDate, status, stage, group, matchday, homeTeam{id,name}, awayTeam{id,name},
136	    score{winner, duration, fullTime{home,away}, halfTime{home,away}}`.
137	  - `status` ∈ `FINISHED | IN_PLAY | PAUSED | TIMED | SCHEDULED`.
138	  - `stage` ∈ `GROUP_STAGE | LAST_32 | LAST_16 | QUARTER_FINALS | SEMI_FINALS | THIRD_PLACE | FINAL`
139	    (counts: 72/16/8/4/2/1/1). **`LAST_32` = Round of 32.**
140	  - `group` ∈ `GROUP_A … GROUP_L` (12 groups) or `null` for knockouts.
141	  - `score.winner` ∈ `HOME_TEAM | AWAY_TEAM | DRAW | null`; `fullTime.home/away` are `null` until played.
142	  - Filter supported: `?stage=LAST_32`.
143	  - **Knockout slot teams are `null`** (homeTeam.name == null) until the groups resolve — DO NOT expect
144	    the bracket from the API; derive it (see bracket-slotting task below).
145	- `GET /v4/competitions/WC/standings` → `{standings:[{stage,type,group,table[]}]}`, **12 groups**.
146	  - `table[]` row: `position, team{id,name}, playedGames, form, won, draw, lost, points, goalsFor,
147	    goalsAgainst, goalDifference` — live group tables for conditioning the sim.
148	
149	### Elo — COMPUTE from martj42 (no clean eloratings.net API)
150	- Do **not** scrape eloratings.net. Compute World Football Elo from `results.csv` chronologically:
151	  `R' = R + K·G·(W − We)`, with K by match importance (Friendly < Qualifier < Continental < World Cup),
152	  G a goal-margin multiplier, `We = 1/(1+10^(-dr/400))` and `dr = home_elo − away_elo + home_adv`
153	  (`home_adv = 0` when `neutral`). Emit per-team, per-date Elo + pre-match Elo-diff.
154	
155	### FIFA ranking (cnc8/fifa-world-ranking) — feature, but STALE
156	- `master/fifa_ranking-2020-12-10.csv` — **62,425 rows**:
157	  `id, rank, country_full, country_abrv, total_points, previous_points, rank_change, confederation, rank_date`.
158	- **Ends 2020-12-10** → for current points use a fresher pull (Kaggle `cashncarry/fifaworldranking`,
159	  updated) or scrape fifa.com. The `confederation` column (UEFA/CONMEBOL/CAF/AFC/CONCACAF/OFC) is a
160	  ready covariate either way; if rankings are unavailable, derive confederation from a static map.
161	
162	### Bookmaker odds (backtest baseline only — NOT a feature)
163	- `football-data.co.uk` (e.g. `mmz4281/2324/E0.csv`) = **club** leagues, columns include match stats
164	  (`FTHG,FTAG,FTR,HS,AS,HST,AST,HC,AC…`) and 1X2 odds (`B365H/D/A, PSH/D/A, WHH/D/A, VCH…`). Useful as the
165	  **de-vig reference** (`p_i = (1/o_i) / Σ(1/o_j)`), NOT for WC outright odds.
166	- Historical **WC** outright/match odds (2014/18/22) must be **scraped** (oddsportal/archived) and cached.
167	
168	### Team-name normalization (REQUIRED)
169	- martj42 and football-data.org names can differ (e.g. `Türkiye`/`Turkey`, `Czechia`, `South Korea`,
170	  `United States`/`USA`, `IR Iran`). Build a crosswalk dict so live results join to historical training.
171	
172	### WC2026 bracket-slotting (REQUIRED — knockout teams are not in the API)
173	- 48 teams → 12 groups → **top 2 of each group + 8 best third-placed** advance to the Round of 32.
174	- Encode the official WC2026 R32 bracket template (which group-winner / runner-up / best-third meets
175	  whom) **and** the best-third-place selection/assignment rules, so the simulator can resolve `LAST_32`
176	  from simulated final group standings.
177	
178	## Additional Notes
179	
180	### Football modeling logic (what to implement)
181	- **Poisson goal model:** goals ~ Poisson(λ), λ = f(attack_i, defence_j, home_adv); predict scoreline → W/D/L.
182	- **Dixon-Coles:** add `rho` low-score correction + exponential time-decay (recent matches weigh more).
183	- **Elo / World Football Elo:** rating updated by result × margin × importance; Elo-diff → win prob.
184	- **Groll hybrid:** feed time-weighted Poisson abilities + Elo + covariates into a Random Forest /
185	  gradient boosting — beats either component alone (arXiv 1806.03208).
186	- **Why goal-based ≫ the old classifier:** keeps goal margin → enables group goal-difference tiebreaks,
187	  models draws, simulates any matchup. A win/loss classifier cannot produce tournament standings.
188	- **Neutral venue:** WC2026 host cities are neutral → `home_advantage = 0` for neutral matches.
189	- **Draws:** group = W/D/L + goal-diff; knockout = extra time (`λ×0.33`) then penalty coin-flip.
190	- **Bookmaker odds:** the benchmark to beat (de-vig consensus). Here used only for evaluation.
191	- **Monte Carlo:** condition on played results → simulate the rest → repeat ~100k → title odds.
192	
193	### Prior work (reference methods)
194	- Groll/Ley/Schauberger/Van Eetvelde hybrid RF — arXiv 1806.03208; reproduced for WC2022/2026.
195	- Leitner-Zeileis-Hornik bookmaker consensus — predicted 2010 winner + 3/4 of 2014 semifinalists.
196	- Dixon-Coles 1997 (JRSS C 46(2):265–280) — foundational goal model.
197	- Robberechts-Davis (KU Leuven) — Elo-diff ordered logit best 2002–2014 (acc 0.5938, RPS 0.1860).
198	- Egidi-Torelli — double Poisson beat result-classifiers on Brier (small sample, inconclusive).
199	
200	### Data stack (no-key training; key only for live)
201	- **martj42/international_results** (CC0) — all international matches 1872→present. **Primary training.**
202	- **football-data.org** (key in `.env`) — live WC2026 standings/results/remaining fixtures only.
203	- **eloratings.net** / computed Elo — World Football Elo features.
204	- **FIFA rankings** (Kaggle cnc8/cashncarry) — ranking feature.
205	- Historical WC **odds scraped** (2014/18/22) — backtest baseline only.
206	
207	### Caveats
208	- Literature metric wins are small-sample (Egidi-Torelli Brier edge = 16 matches; inconclusive).
209	- WC2026 mostly neutral venues → standard home-advantage does not apply.
210	- WC2026 hybrid result is a June 2026 blog reproduction, not peer-reviewed.
211	- `0.33` extra-time multiplier + coin-flip shootout are implementation choices, not standards.
212	- Odds/Elo scrapers are fragile — cache and degrade gracefully; verify licensing before shipping.
213	
