lass), `multiclass_log_loss`, `brier_score` (3-class W/D/L) — each unit-tested against hand-computed values on tiny known arrays.\n- [ ] A `backtest_hybrid` orchestrator slices played WC matches per tournament-year (2014/18/22) on time-aware splits, predicts W/D/L with the hybrid, and returns a comparison table vs the bookmaker baseline (from #20) and vs the legacy classifier.\n- [ ] RPS is reported as the primary metric; log-loss and Brier reported alongside.\n- [ ] Backtest degrades gracefully when odds are unavailable (skips the bookmaker column, still compares hybrid vs legacy).\n- [ ] All tests pass; new `tests/test_evaluation_metrics.py` (exact metric values) and `tests/test_backtest.py` (synthetic 2-tournament frame, stub hybrid + stub odds → comparison table).\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #16: feat: Cycle 5 config groundwork — [rf]/[odds] sections, knockout sim params, TOML wiring\n- #20: feat: archived bookmaker odds scraper + de-vig + CSV cache (data/odds.py)\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Modify:** `worldcup_playoff/models/evaluation.py` — add the three pure metric functions (keep them small and import-light). If adding the backtest orchestration would push the file past ~500 lines, **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/models/backtest.py` for the `backtest_hybrid` orchestration and keep only the metrics in `evaluation.py`.\n- **Create:** `tests/test_evaluation_metrics.py` — assert exact RPS/log-loss/Brier on hand-computed arrays.\n- **Create:** `tests/test_backtest.py` — synthetic frame + stub hybrid/odds → assert the comparison table shape and the graceful-no-odds path.\n- Consume `chronological_split`/`build_dataset` from `models/dataset.py` — never shuffle. Bookmaker odds are a baseline only, never passed into model features.","labels":[{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIFhg","name":"priority:high","description":"High priority","color":"FF0000"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopII0g","name":"phase:implement","description":"Phase: implement","color":"D4C5F9"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIKMQ","name":"agent:python-pro","description":"Agent: python-pro","color":"7057FF"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACoqtFUA","name":"area:models","description":"Area: models","color":"0052CC"}],"milestone":{"number":5,"title":"Cycle 5 — Tournament Simulation & Full Pipeline","description":"Extend tournament simulator: ingest played WC2026 results as fixed, simulate remaining group matches (correct tiebreak rules: goal-diff, goals-for, head-to-head, coin-flip), resolve Round of 32 from standings, simulate knockout (extra time λ×0.33 → penalty coin-flip), run ~100k Monte Carlo → full title odds + per-round advancement for all 48 teams. Historical odds scraper (backtest baseline: de-vig WC2014/18/22 from archived sources, cache to CSV). Evaluation metrics: RPS (primary), log-loss, Brier on time-aware splits. Config: add [poisson], [elo], [rf], [odds], [live] sections (Pydantic + TOML). CLI: new commands fetch-live, build-features, train-hybrid, backtest, forecast (live title odds) + existing bracket/PNG.","dueOn":null},"state":"OPEN","title":"feat: probabilistic eval metrics (RPS/log-loss/Brier) + hybrid backtest vs bookmaker baseline"}
