default (martj42 schedule), accepts an optional config/seed/n-simulations, and prints/saves full title odds + per-round advancement; re-runnable.\n- [ ] Existing commands (`download/clean/train/fit/simulate/bracket/run`) remain registered and unchanged; existing PNG outputs intact.\n- [ ] All tests pass; `tests/test_cli.py` extended with `CliRunner` smoke tests for each new command (exit code 0) against monkeypatched module calls (no network, no heavy compute).\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #19: feat: ~100k Monte-Carlo live-forecast orchestrator + title odds (simulation/live_forecast.py)\n- #21: feat: probabilistic eval metrics (RPS/log-loss/Brier) + hybrid backtest vs bookmaker baseline\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Modify:** `worldcup_playoff/cli.py` — add the five commands following the `simulate`/`bracket` pattern (`cli.py:551-644`), reusing the existing logging + Rich `Progress` helpers. If `cli.py` approaches the ~500-600 line ceiling, factor the new command bodies into a thin `worldcup_playoff/cli_forecast.py` and register them on the shared `app`.\n- **Modify:** `tests/test_cli.py` — add `CliRunner` smoke tests per command with module functions monkeypatched; snapshot/assert the full command list still includes the legacy commands.\n- Keep heavy compute (sims, fitting, scraping) inside the pipeline/modules; commands stay thin orchestration wrappers.\n- `forecast` no-key default is a hard requirement: a missing API key must degrade to the martj42 schedule, never error.","labels":[{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIFhg","name":"priority:high","description":"High priority","color":"FF0000"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIF7g","name":"area:cli","description":"Area: cli","color":"0052CC"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopII0g","name":"phase:implement","description":"Phase: implement","color":"D4C5F9"},{"id":"LA_kwDOTBxfPc8AAAACopIKMQ","name":"agent:python-pro","description":"Agent: python-